itler's horrors and his effort to broaden immigration policy. She also recounts the importance of their religious convictions, their controversial standing among Quebecers, and their early advocacy of official bilingualism. An invigorating and well-told tale of their lasting legacies, Georges and Pauline Vanier is the definitive account of the enduring contributions the Vaniers made to the world and to their country.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAmbassadorszCanadavBiography. 0aAmbassadors' spouseszCanadavBiography. 0aGovernors generalzCanadavBiography. 0aGovernors general's spouseszCanadavBiography. 0aSoldierszCanadavBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Political.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077358579940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773585799423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773585799/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles